Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 200, 31. Name Kallikrates. Most probably Kallikrates III.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0592)
